Space the rollers evenly along the tractor bar.
Space the paper guides evenly on the paper chute.
Lock the sprocket in place.
Put the paper chute in the raised position by lifting it firmly.
Open the tractor cover.
Unlock the sprocket.
Unlock the other sprocket.
Position it in accordance with the paper width.
Open the sprocket covers.
Position the holes in the paper over the two sprockets.
Adjust the two sliders on the tractor cover in alignment with the rollers.
Put the paper chute in the down position.
Gently lift it towards the back of the printer.
Make sure that the paper support bar is in the closed position.
Place the lever in the position marked for drawing.
Close the cover firmly.
Close the seat cover.
Close the sprocket cover.
If the printer is powered off, power it on (see Section 3).
Position 1 is available only if you open the cover.
If it is not already positioned, slide to the right.
The display shows “Load”.
The paper must be inserted at the rear of the printer.
You can select different positions for paper loading.
It clips into place.